<task id="AIPU2-010" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build CapabilityManifest Singleton</title>
    <phase>2A</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, capabilities</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-006</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    Build a CapabilityManifest singleton that caches all AI capabilities from Dataverse in memory at startup.
    This is the central registry that the capability router (Layer 1, 2, 3) and the orchestrator prompt builder
    both depend on. It must load synchronously before any AI request is served and expose sub-millisecond
    read access. All subsequent Phase 2A and 2B tasks read from this manifest, so correctness and low-latency
    access are the top priorities.
  </prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET backend engineer familiar with Spaarke BFF API patterns, Dataverse, and AI orchestration.</role>
  <goal>
    CapabilityManifest singleton loads all active capabilities from Dataverse on BFF startup, exposes a
    thread-safe in-memory dictionary, and returns any capability by name in under 1ms. Contains at minimum:
    capability display name, description, keyword hints, associated playbook ID, tool set, and enabled flag.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/ai.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgentFactory.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/ServiceCollectionExtensions.cs</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read SprkChatAgentFactory.cs and the existing AI service registration in ServiceCollectionExtensions.cs to understand current capability loading patterns.</step>
    <step>Create CapabilityManifestEntry.cs record in Services/Ai/Capabilities/ with properties: CapabilityName (string), Description (string), KeywordHints (IReadOnlyList&lt;string&gt;), PlaybookId (Guid?), ToolNames (IReadOnlyList&lt;string&gt;), IsEnabled (bool), TenantRestrictions (IReadOnlyList&lt;string&gt;).</step>
    <step>Create ICapabilityManifest.cs interface with: TryGet(string name, out CapabilityManifestEntry entry), GetAll(), LastRefreshedUtc property.</step>
    <step>Create CapabilityManifest.cs implementing ICapabilityManifest as a singleton backed by ImmutableDictionary&lt;string, CapabilityManifestEntry&gt; (swap-on-refresh pattern using Interlocked.Exchange).</step>
    <step>Create ICapabilityManifestLoader.cs interface with LoadAsync(CancellationToken) returning IReadOnlyList&lt;CapabilityManifestEntry&gt;.</step>
    <step>Create DataverseCapabilityManifestLoader.cs implementing ICapabilityManifestLoader, querying the sprk_aicapability Dataverse table via the existing IDataverseService (or direct OData client). Map columns to CapabilityManifestEntry fields.</step>
    <step>In CapabilityManifest, add InitializeAsync(CancellationToken) called from an IHostedService startup hook (or existing startup pipeline). Throw if Dataverse is unreachable and no cached snapshot exists.</step>
    <step>Register ICapabilityManifest (singleton), ICapabilityManifestLoader, and DataverseCapabilityManifestLoader in AddAiCapabilitiesModule() extension method on IServiceCollection.</step>
    <step>Write unit tests in tests/ covering: TryGet returns correct entry, GetAll returns all enabled entries, swap-on-refresh replaces dictionary atomically, disabled entries are excluded from GetAll.</step>
    <step>Verify BFF startup sequence: run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` and confirm no build errors.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>CapabilityManifest is registered as a singleton and populated before the first HTTP request is handled.</criterion>
    <criterion>TryGet and GetAll complete in under 1ms on a loaded manifest (verified by unit test stopwatch assertion).</criterion>
    <criterion>Disabled capabilities (IsEnabled = false) are excluded from GetAll() results.</criterion>
    <criterion>ImmutableDictionary swap is atomic — no lock required on the read path.</criterion>
    <criterion>Unit tests pass: `dotnet test --filter "CapabilityManifest"`.</criterion>
    <criterion>Build succeeds with no new warnings: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
